
[1]speculm

   SPEC'ULM, n. [L.]

   1. A mirror or looking glass.

   2. A glass that reflects the images of objects.

   3. A metallic reflector used in catadioptric telescopes.

   4. In surgery, an instrument for dilating and keeping open certain
   parts of the body.
